definitions: describing land that is left unplanted for a period to restore fertility
examples: The fallow fields will be planted next spring
Farmers left several acres fallow this season

definitions: contrary to fact or truth, presenting incorrect or misleading information
made to imitate something in order to deceive or substitute
examples: His false statement misled the investigators completely
The witness gave false testimony under oath
She wore false eyelashes to the party
The painting turned out to be a false masterpiece

definitions: describing a voice that is artificially high in pitch, especially in male singers
examples: The singer's falsetto voice reached incredible high notes
He sang the chorus in a beautiful falsetto

definitions: moving unsteadily or hesitantly, showing signs of weakness or uncertainty
examples: Her faltering steps showed how tired she was
The company's faltering profits worried the investors

definitions: having widespread recognition and reputation for excellence or achievement
examples: The famed artist's work sells for millions
We visited the famed landmarks of ancient Rome

definitions: concerning or characteristic of a family or its members and relationships
examples: The familial bond between siblings remained strong
Doctors studied the familial pattern of the disease

definitions: showing excessive enthusiasm and intense devotion, especially to a cause or activity
examples: The fanatic supporters never missed a single game
She's fanatic about keeping her workspace organized

definitions: filled with excessive and single-minded zeal, especially about religious or political matters
examples: His fanatical dedication to fitness impressed everyone
The group's fanatical beliefs worried their families

definitions: existing only in imagination or appearing to be true without proof
considered likely to succeed or win in competition
examples: Her fancied illness had no medical basis
The child's fancied monsters kept him awake
The fancied horse won the race easily
They were the fancied team in the tournament

definitions: existing only in imagination and unlikely to become reality, highly creative
examples: The architect's fanciful designs were beautiful but impractical
Children often have fanciful ideas about their futures

definitions: arranged or spread out in the shape of an open fan
examples: The peacock's fanned tail displayed brilliant colors
The cards were fanned across the table

definitions: based on fantasy rather than reality, imaginative to the point of being bizarre
extraordinary and seemingly impossible, having a dreamlike or magical quality
examples: The movie featured fantastical creatures and magical worlds
Her fantastical stories entertained the children for hours
The palace had fantastical architecture unlike anything else
Scientists made fantastical discoveries in the deep ocean

definitions: located at a great distance from the observer or reference point
having a dreamy, distracted quality suggesting thoughts are elsewhere
examples: They traveled to faraway countries every summer
The faraway mountains looked blue in the distance
She had a faraway look in her eyes
His faraway expression showed he wasn't listening

definitions: resembling a farce in being absurd, ridiculous, or improbable to the point of comedy
examples: The trial became farcical when witnesses contradicted themselves
Their farcical attempts at cooking ended in disaster

definitions: concerned with or used in the cultivation of land and raising of crops or livestock
examples: The farming community gathered for the harvest festival
Modern farming techniques increase crop yields significantly

definitions: at or to a greater distance in space compared to another point
examples: The farther shore was barely visible through fog
We need to walk farther to reach the summit

definitions: at or to the greatest distance from a particular point or place
examples: Neptune is the farthest planet from the sun
The farthest corner of the room was dark

definitions: having one's interest or curiosity strongly engaged by something captivating or compelling
examples: The fascinated audience watched the magician's every move
She was fascinated by ancient Egyptian history

definitions: relating to or characteristic of fascism, showing extreme authoritarian and intolerant views
examples: The fascist regime suppressed all political opposition
His fascist attitudes made democratic discussion impossible

definitions: conforming to or following what is currently popular in style, design, or practice
examples: She always wore the most fashionable clothes
The fashionable restaurant was fully booked every night

definitions: created, constructed, or given form in a particular way or style
examples: The beautifully fashioned jewelry caught everyone's attention
The cabin was fashioned from local pine logs

definitions: fixed firmly in position or closed securely using a device or method
examples: The fastened seatbelt kept her safe during turbulence
Make sure all windows are properly fastened

definitions: showing or demanding excessive delicacy, care, or attention to detail and cleanliness
examples: Her fastidious nature meant every detail was perfect
The fastidious editor caught every small error

definitions: causing or capable of causing death through injury or disease
leading inevitably to failure, disaster, or ruin in a situation
examples: The accident resulted in fatal injuries to the driver
The disease can be fatal if left untreated
His fatal mistake cost the company millions
Ignoring customer feedback proved fatal to the business

definitions: certain to happen because of fate or a power beyond human control
examples: Their fated meeting changed both their lives forever
The fated expedition never returned from the Arctic

definitions: having far-reaching and typically negative consequences for future events or outcomes
examples: The fateful decision to invade changed history
It was a fateful day when they first met

definitions: having no father because of death, absence, or abandonment
examples: The fatherless children were raised by their grandmother
Support groups help fatherless families cope with challenges

definitions: showing the affectionate care and protective concern typically associated with fathers
examples: His fatherly advice helped guide her career choices
The coach took a fatherly interest in players

definitions: suffering from extreme physical or mental tiredness resulting from exertion
examples: The fatigued soldiers could barely stay awake
She felt fatigued after working double shifts

definitions: containing a large amount of fat or having the characteristics of fat
examples: The doctor advised avoiding fatty foods
Fatty tissue surrounded the internal organs

definitions: having no faults, defects, or errors; perfect in execution or quality
examples: Her faultless performance earned a standing ovation
The diamond's faultless clarity made it valuable

definitions: containing faults, defects, or errors that prevent proper functioning
examples: The faulty wiring caused the house fire
His faulty reasoning led to wrong conclusions

definitions: made to look like something else, especially something more expensive or genuine
examples: She wore a beautiful faux fur coat
The faux marble countertops looked surprisingly real

definitions: creating advantageous conditions or increasing the chances of success
expressing approval, support, or a positive opinion about something
examples: The favorable weather conditions helped the harvest
Market conditions are favorable for new investments
The movie received favorable reviews from critics
Her boss gave a favorable assessment of her work

definitions: given special treatment, preference, or advantage over others in a situation
examples: The favored candidate won by a large margin
She was the favored child in the family

definitions: creating advantageous conditions or increasing the chances of success
expressing approval, support, or a positive opinion about something
examples: The favourable winds helped them reach port early
Business conditions remain favourable for expansion
The committee gave a favourable response to proposals
Critics offered favourable comments about the exhibition

definitions: preferred above all others of the same kind; most liked
examples: Chocolate ice cream is my favourite dessert
This is her favourite dress for special occasions

definitions: experiencing or showing fear, anxiety, or apprehension about something
causing fear or worry; frightening or concerning in nature
examples: The fearful child hid behind his mother
She was fearful of making the wrong decision
The fearful storm damaged many homes
They faced fearful consequences for their actions

definitions: showing a lack of fear in the face of danger or difficulty
examples: The fearless explorer ventured into unknown territories
Her fearless journalism exposed widespread corruption

definitions: causing fear or respect through being impressively large, powerful, or capable
examples: The fearsome dragon guarded the castle entrance
Their fearsome reputation preceded them into battle

definitions: capable of being done, accomplished, or carried out successfully with available resources
examples: The committee decided the plan was financially feasible
Is it feasible to complete this by Friday?

definitions: having feathers as a covering, especially as a natural characteristic of birds
examples: The feathered creatures built nests in the trees
Her feathered hat was the height of fashion

definitions: having a light, soft, delicate quality resembling feathers in appearance or texture
examples: The feathery clouds drifted across the blue sky
She had feathery blonde hair that caught the light

definitions: given special attention or prominence in a presentation, display, or publication
examples: The featured artist displayed her best works
This week's featured products are on sale

definitions: without distinctive or interesting features, qualities, or characteristics; plain and unremarkable
examples: The featureless desert stretched endlessly before them
His featureless face was hard to remember

definitions: of, relating to, or consisting of feces or solid bodily waste
examples: The doctor ordered fecal tests for the patient
Fecal contamination made the water supply unsafe

definitions: joined together in a federation with shared power between central and regional authorities
examples: The federated states maintained some independent powers
Several small companies formed a federated organization

definitions: lacking physical strength or health, especially from age or illness
lacking force, effectiveness, or conviction in action or expression
examples: His feeble attempts to stand required assistance
The elderly woman's feeble voice was barely audible
She made a feeble excuse for being late
The team's feeble effort disappointed their fans

definitions: simulated or pretended in order to deceive or give a false impression
examples: Her feigned surprise didn't fool anyone at the party
He showed feigned interest in the boring presentation

definitions: showing courage, determination, and spirited resistance despite small size or perceived weakness
examples: The feisty little dog barked at larger animals
Her feisty personality made her a natural leader
